CNCP v1 23179
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#8603: Teleport rendered before async dependencies resolve in Suspense component",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:24:16.221764+00:00",
  "text": "Teleport rendered before async dependencies resolve in Suspense component\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.3.4\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSee reproduction link.\r\n\r\n```\r\n<Suspense>\r\n  <div>\r\n    <AsyncComp />\r\n    <div>This will only render once the AsyncComp is resolved</div>\r\n    <Teleport to=\"body\">This is rendered immediately</Teleport>\r\n  </div>\r\n</Suspense>\r\n```\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe `Teleport` is only rendered once the async dependencies of the `Suspense` resolve. \n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nThe `Teleport` is rendered immediately, before the async dependencies of the `Suspense` resolve. \n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: suspense",
    "scope: teleport"
  ],
